# Ross Simmonds: LinkedIn Content Collection

## Post 1: The Marketing Epiphany (Distribution > Creation)
- **Link:** https://www.linkedin.com/posts/rosssimmonds_every-marketer-has-had-this-moment-you-activity-7445892892096745472-alZk
- **Topic:** Content Strategy & Mindset
- **Analysis:** Ross addresses the common frustration of "content anxiety"—spending weeks on a piece only for it to get zero reach. He argues that the moment of success happens when a marketer stops obsessing over the "perfect" creative and starts obsessing over where that creative lives. 
- **Key Takeaway:** If you aren't spending as much time on the distribution plan as you did on the writing, you aren't marketing; you're just typing.

## Post 2: Visibility in LLMs & AI Optimization
- **Link:** https://www.linkedin.com/posts/rosssimmonds_visibility-in-llms-how-distribution-opens-activity-7448852393817063424-ctrF
- **Topic:** The Future of SEO / AI-Driven Marketing
- **Analysis:** This is a cutting-edge post about "AIO" (AI Optimization). Ross explains that being mentioned by AI agents (like ChatGPT or Gemini) in 2026 depends on how well your content is distributed across niche communities and LinkedIn. Distribution isn't just for humans anymore; it's how you train the AI models to recognize your brand as an authority.
- **Key Takeaway:** Modern distribution is about "winning the training data." The more places your insights appear, the more likely AI is to recommend your SaaS.